---
import { Download, FileText, X } from "@lucide/astro";
---

<button
  type="button"
  class="btn btn-primary mt-5 gap-2"
  onclick="document.getElementById('resume-modal')?.showModal()"
>
  <FileText class="size-5" />
  Resume
</button>

<dialog id="resume-modal" class="modal">
  <div
    class="modal-box flex max-h-[86vh] w-11/12 max-w-5xl flex-col overflow-hidden rounded-lg p-0 text-left"
  >
    <div
      class="flex shrink-0 items-start justify-between gap-3 border-b border-base-300 bg-base-100 px-5 py-4"
    >
      <div class="min-w-0">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold leading-tight">Alistair O'Brien</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
          Senior Game/Tools Programmer
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-base-content/70">
          Osaka, Japan | alistair.m.obrien@gmail.com |
          <a
            class="link link-primary"
            href="https://jp.linkedin.com/in/alistair-o-brien"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            jp.linkedin.com/in/alistair-o-brien
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-2">
        <a
          class="btn btn-sm btn-primary gap-2"
          href="/alistair-obrien-resume.pdf"
          download="alistair-obrien-resume.pdf"
        >
          <Download class="size-4" />
          PDF
        </a>
        <form method="dialog">
          <button class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost btn-circle" aria-label="Close resume">
            <X class="size-5" />
          </button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>

    <article class="resume-document min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-5 py-5 sm:px-8 sm:py-7">
      <section>
        <h2>Professional Summary</h2>
        <p>
          Senior game/tools programmer with experience across Unity, C#, tools
          development, game systems architecture, console porting, production
          workflows, and technical art. Strong focus on building practical tools
          and pipelines that reduce friction for designers, artists, programmers,
          and other collaborators. Shipped work spans PC, Nintendo Switch,
          PlayStation, Xbox, Android, Web.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Core Skills</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Programming:</strong> C#, Unity, Python</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Game development:</strong> Core Gameplay Architecture, Combat
            Systems, UI Frameworks, Animation Tooling, Procedural Generation,
            Localization, Debug/Diagnostics Tooling
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Platforms:</strong> Windows, macOS, iOS, Android, web,
            Nintendo Switch, PlayStation, Xbox
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Production:</strong> Project Scheduling, Budgeting, Publisher
            Communications, Workflow Design, Dev Ops
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Professional Experience</h2>

        <h3>Skeleton Crew Studio - Senior Programmer</h3>
        <p class="meta">Kyoto, Japan | October 2019 - Present</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Built game systems architecture, internal tools, and production
            workflows across games, VR, web, experimental experiences, and
            non-game projects.
          </li>
          <li>
            Led workflow optimization and tool development efforts to ensure
            designers and artists had minimum friction when implementing their
            visions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Contributed to console porting work, including graphics optimization,
            memory management, CPU performance, input, and platform-specific
            compliance.
          </li>
          <li>
            Led production and project management through scheduling, budgeting,
            and efficient communication processes.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="subhead">Selected projects:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong
              >Forestrike - Lead Programmer / Producer, Unity, C#, Python,
              Windows, Nintendo Switch</strong
            >
            <ul>
              <li>
                Designed project schedule, budget, milestone structure, and
                development workflow for a martial arts roguelite published by
                Devolver Digital.
              </li>
              <li>
                Built a custom Aseprite importer and combat animation sequencer
                for designer-authored combat behavior.
              </li>
              <li>Created designer-facing player technique tooling.</li>
              <li>
                Designed a localization system which favored in context editing
                and enabled late-stage localization kit export.
              </li>
              <li>
                Built an asset-driven audio layer with audio designer friendly
                parameters which reduced manual AudioSource management.
              </li>
              <li>
                Set up remote build deployment systems and workflows to ensure
                rapid testing processes were non interrupting.
              </li>
              <li>
                Optimized the Nintendo Switch version for graphics, memory, CPU
                bottlenecks, and implemented correct authentication processes for
                independent server communication.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong
              >Olija - Programmer, Unity, C#, Construct 2, Windows, Nintendo
              Switch, PlayStation, Xbox</strong
            >
            <ul>
              <li>Supported multi-platform porting.</li>
              <li>Documented and automated platform build processes.</li>
              <li>Built debug overlays and investigated niche platform-specific bugs.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Active Gaming Media - Programmer</h3>
        <p class="meta">Osaka, Japan | March 2018 - October 2019</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Worked in a small in-house game development department using Unity
            and C#.
          </li>
          <li>
            Led a team of roughly eight developers, with emphasis on project
            management and smoother development workflows.
          </li>
          <li>
            Developed tools and Unity systems to support production needs and
            reduce repeated manual work.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Scarlet City Studios - Programmer / 3D Artist</h3>
        <p class="meta">Auckland, New Zealand | December 2013 - July 2017</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Started as a 3D and texture artist, moved into technical art, then
            transitioned into programming.
          </li>
          <li>
            Created hand-painted low-poly game assets using Blender, Photoshop,
            and Unity.
          </li>
          <li>
            Built mobile-friendly shaders for vertex animation, color remapping,
            and ambient effects.
          </li>
          <li>
            Implemented combat system frontend work, quest content, and game
            designer tools for animation timelines.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="subhead">Selected project:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong
              >The Aetherlight - Programmer / 3D Artist, Unity, C#, Java,
              Blender, Photoshop, Windows, macOS, iOS, Android, web</strong
            >
            <ul>
              <li>
                Contributed 3D art, technical art, shader work, combat tooling,
                and frontend gameplay programming.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Education</h2>
        <h3>Auckland University of Technology</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          Auckland, New Zealand | Bachelor of Art and Design, Digital Design |
          2011 - 2013
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Graduated as Head of School.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
  <form method="dialog" class="modal-backdrop">
    <button>close</button>
  </form>
</dialog>

<style>
  .resume-document {
    background: var(--fallback-b1, oklch(var(--b1)));
    color: var(--fallback-bc, oklch(var(--bc)));
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .resume-document section {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .resume-document h2 {
    margin: 1rem 0 0.4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in oklch, currentColor 28%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 0.2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .resume-document h3 {
    margin: 0.8rem 0 0.2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .resume-document p {
    margin: 0.25rem 0;
  }

  .resume-document ul {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.65rem 1.2rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .resume-document li {
    margin: 0.2rem 0;
  }

  .resume-document .meta {
    color: color-mix(in oklch, currentColor 72%, transparent);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .resume-document .subhead {
    margin-top: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
